modules.description: This module implements a Unix-based key-value store with support for both read-only and read-write operations. It provides functions to manipulate key-value pairs, including setting, removing, renaming, and partial updates of values, as well as querying existence, size, modification time, and digests. It works directly with string values and hierarchical keys, making it suitable for file system emulation, configuration storage, or embedded data management where direct disk access is needed.
